      • PROP_DROP_ANNOTATIONS

        static final String PROP_DROP_ANNOTATIONS

        A list of annotations that should be ignored during conversion. Annotations are defined as {phrase|word|morph}::{language}:name, of which the layer (the first) and the language (the second) element are optional. languages is a reserved name and will drop all language meta annotations from the child elements of <languages/>.

        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • PROP_ANNOTATIONMAP

        static final String PROP_ANNOTATIONMAP

        A map whose keys are FLEx annotation and whose values are annotations they should be mapped to.

        Syntax:

        • keys: {interlinear-text|paragraph|phrase|word|morph}::{language}:name
        • values: name
        • list: key=value, ...

        Behaviour:

        For annotations matching the key pattern, the name will be changed to the name value. language will not be changed, layer neither.

        Example:

        annotationMap=word::en:gls=ge will change the FLEx-notated annotation <word><item type="gls" lang="en">green</item></word> to an SAnnotation on an SLayer named “word” with namespace “en” and name “ge”.

        See Also:
        Constant Field Values
